  "text": "Needless to say, drug-eluting stents (DESs) significantly reduce the risk of restenosis after percutaneous coronary intervention (PCI). However, effects of DES implantation have been limited in patients on maintenance hemodialysis (HD) [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
